                   Guide for Developing Security Plans for Federal Information Systems


Configuration      Process for controlling modifications to hardware, firmware,
Control            software, and documentation to ensure that the information system is
[CNSS Inst.        protected against improper modifications before, during, and after
4009]              system implementation.
Countermeasures    Actions, devices, procedures, techniques, or other measures that
[CNSS Inst.        reduce the vulnerability of an information system. Synonymous with
4009]              security controls and safeguards.
Executive          An executive department specified in 5 U.S.C., Sec. 101; a military
Agency             department specified in 5 U.S.C., Sec. 102; an independent
[41 U.S.C., Sec.   establishment as defined in 5 U.S.C., Sec. 104(1); and a wholly
403]               owned Government corporation fully subject to the provisions of 31
                   U.S.C., Chapter 91.
Federal            A business-based framework for government-wide improvement
Enterprise         developed by the Office of Management and Budget that is intended
Architecture       to facilitate efforts to transform the federal government to one that is
[FEA Program       citizen-centered, results-oriented, and market-based.
Management
Office]
Federal            An information system used or operated by an executive agency, by a
Information        contractor of an executive agency, or by another organization on
System             behalf of an executive agency.
[40 U.S.C., Sec.
11331]
General Support    An interconnected set of information resources under the same direct
System             management control that shares common functionality. It normally
[OMB Circular      includes hardware, software, information, data, applications,
A-130,             communications, and people.
Appendix III]
High-Impact        An information system in which at least one security objective (i.e.,
System             confidentiality, integrity, or availability) is assigned a FIPS 199
                   potential impact value of high.
Information        Official with statutory or operational authority for specified
Owner              information and responsibility for establishing the controls for its
[CNSS Inst.        generation, collection, processing, dissemination, and disposal.
4009]
Information        Information and related resources, such as personnel, equipment,
Resources          funds, and information technology.
